values:
So Christmas break wasn't too shabby. I enjoyed it. I got to see some people...the ones that love me anyways...I'm just joking.&nbsp;

Interesting stories though have come out of it. For example, I have come to learn that my little cousin refers to Santa as Ho Ho. This is all fine and cute, but I don't think that any one should go around saying "I went and saw Ho Ho." Some people wouldn't take it as Santa. Another interesting fact I have come to find is that one of my other little cousins agrees with me that boys have cooties. This being interesting due to the fact that he is a boy. I love my family.

I've also come to the conclusion that the cops in Algona need to find something to occupy their time with.&nbsp;I'm highly entertained by the fact that a cop had the time to pull me over to tell me that my car was&nbsp;dirty. I may have glasses and have to wear them at night to drive, but I could see that my car was dirty. I don't believe that it was as dirty as he believed it to be, but the cops are always right...or so they think. I have to say though, that I&nbsp; am impressed that they are such caring citizens that they will go out of their way to tell me the obvious. And just to set the record straight, my car is maroon, not red; the officer couldn't tell the difference, I guess, under all that dirt...ha ha ha.&nbsp;

love to all, merry late Christmas, and happy new year!
